radiographic_examinations.findings: Subsegmental atelectasis at the lung bases, two hypoattenuating lesions in the left lobe of the liver (14 mm and 17 mm), a 1.7 x 2.7 x 1.5 cm hypoattenuating lesion in the posterior right lobe of the liver, fluid-filled appendix measuring 10 mm with significant periappendiceal fat stranding, no pleural effusion, no intra- or extra-hepatic biliary duct dilatation, and no evidence of perforation.
